summary:
Determining the situation in Sudan continues to threaten international peace and security, 
1. Decides to extend UNMIS's mandate until 31 October 2007, intending to renew it further; 
2. Requests the Secretary-General to appoint a new Special Representative for Sudan and report to the Council every three months on UNMIS's mandate implementation; 
3. Calls upon parties to the Comprehensive Peace Agreement to accelerate implementation of commitments, particularly on Joint Integrated Units, security sector reforms, disarmament, demobilization, and redeployment of forces by 9 July 2007, border demarcation, Abyei administration, and national elections; 
4. Calls upon parties to various agreements, including the Darfur Peace Agreement, to respect and implement commitments without delay; 
5. Requests the Secretary-General to ensure UNMIS complies with the UN's zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse; 
6. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
